The Democratic Alliance is kicking it up a gear to ignite economic growth and provide access to jobs in the metros they now govern. Party leader Mmusi Maimane met with the mayors of the four DA-led metros of Johannesburg, Tshwane, Cape Town and Nelson Mandela Bay on Tuesday. Each mayor - including Athol Trollip, Solly Msimanga, Patricia De Lille and Herman Mashaba - presented their successes, challenges, and plans going forward to sustain economic growth. This is what the DA plans to do in each of their metros:  Johannesburg Tshwane Cape Town  Nelson Mandela Bay 